Well, so, that's what I did today.
First point of criticism: We need prettier flight logs. Black is boring, pink is not really pink, but salmon-colored.
I wanted to fly since I was little.
And today it finally happened… I flew an airplane today. I haven't fully processed that yet.
Data from Flightaware.
I'm trying to go back again next Saturday. The weather doesn't look too good right now, but it's still Monday.
It's already becoming clear where the problems lie. It will probably be VERY difficult to get the medical permit due to the FAA's opinion on certain medications.
It's not impossible, but it will take a VERY long time and mean a LOT of extra work.
This is somewhat discouraging, but it's just another problem that needs to be solved. So far, it seems solvable. It just costs a lot of time and money.
If you want to know what's ahead of me.
The FAA is not a fan of ADHD. They definitely won't give you a medical clearance if you're taking medication against it.
